==English==
===Etymology===
Old French [[gré]] ‘pleasure, goodwill’, from Latin [[gratum]], a nominal use of the neuter of [[gratus]] ‘pleasing’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /gɹi/

===Noun===
'''gree'''
# [[pleasure]], [[goodwill]], [[satisfaction]]
#:*'''Late C14''': And notified is þurȝout þe toun / Þat every wiȝt, wiþ greet devocioun, / Sholde preyen Crist þat he þis mariage / Recyve in '''gree''' and spede þis viage. — Geoffrey Chaucer, ''The Man of Law's Tale''